cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.CV 

Reasoning: 
- cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely category as the paper is about investigating the ability of RNN language models to represent filler-gap dependencies in natural language. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also likely as the paper discusses state-of-the-art RNN language models and their ability to learn and generalize about empty syntactic positions. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is another possible category as the paper deals with natural language processing and the ability of RNN models to learn and represent syntactic structures. 
- cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is a possible category as the paper discusses the use of RNN models in natural language processing tasks. 
- cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is less likely but still possible as the paper discusses the ability of RNN models to learn and generalize about syntactic structures in natural language, which could be relevant to tasks in computer vision and pattern recognition.
